snippet.textDisplay:
I don't see how Rodgers is to blame , he was going to have to be able to turn water into wine to win this game. I knew we were going to lose after watching the Vikings play them. Packers run game did get better this year but really only because we committed to more then Mike's era and this is the worst WR core The Packers have had in a long time but that didn't even matter when the game is already being lost on the Lines and Rodgers has no time. And yea are defense did get better because we got 3 legit players but no one else was really that great. When you have a new couch come in and change a lot of how Rodgers is use to playing and not haveing really any players on the team for more then a couple of years (besides most of our OL) it was chocking we had as good of a record as we did.


Moving forward it could get weird , i know we can win our division and i think Matt Lafeur's going to build the team up on defense and running as much as he can , yet Rodgers isn't a cheap QB and unless they fix the WR core why even have him on the team. It may take 2-3 years for Lafleur to build the team he wants and idk if the end result will be a winning one.
